<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="lemon-bar" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Lemon Bars</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>2 cups sifted all-purpose flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup confectioners' sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup butter, melted</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>4 eggs</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 cups white sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon baking powder</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup all-purpose flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{5}{8}</m> cup lemon juice</cell>
    </row>
    
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          In a medium bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and confectioners' sugar. Blend in the melted butter. Press into the bottom of a greased 9" x 13" pan. Bake at <m>350^\circ</m> for 15 minutes, or until golden.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          In a large bowl, beat eggs until light. Combine the sugar, baking powder and <m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup of flour so there will be no flour lumps. Stir the sugar mixture into the eggs. Finally, stir in the lemon juice. Pour over the prepared crust.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Bake at <m>350^\circ</m> for 32 minutes.  Allow to cool completely before cutting into bars.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>